==English==

===Etymology===
{{suffix|en|information|ist}}. ''Informationist'' and ''[[informationism]]'' are first known to have arisen in the work of a group of Scottish poets in the 1994 book ''Contraflow on the SuperHighway''.<ref>Price 1993</ref>

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who gathers, analyzes, interprets and uses [[information]], possibly as a [[career]].
# One who practices [[informationism]].

